🔍 What Are Config Files?
These are files that store important project settings, such as which dataset to use, what hyperparameters to try, or which features to include in a model.
Common examples:
config.yml — a structured config file in YAML format (e.g., learning_rate: 0.1)

🔧 Why use them?
Keep your code clean — no hardcoded values!
Easily rerun or modify experiments
Make collaboration smoother

Your config.yml might contain:
target: PM2.5
features:
  - temperature
  - wind_speed
  - traffic_volume
split_ratio: 0.8
model_type: linear_regression
